screenshots.description: Growing Strawberries at a high altitude results in white strawberries, better food, but yield no pips, and can't be crafted into anything.
screenshots.title: White Strawberries

screenshots.description: All the mod's raw food crops can be stored. Some things, like strawberry baskets and banana crates, are only available when quark is installed, however.
screenshots.title: Storage Blocks

screenshots.description: Cocoa beans are now a fair bit more useful. They make chocolate, a food source and uncanny building material.
screenshots.title: Chocolate

screenshots.description: Banana plants can be found in jungles and beaches. Placing their fronds on sand or gravel and having them exposed to rain makes them grow into another banana plant. Bananas themselves allow you to climb all blocks when eaten.
screenshots.title: Bananas

screenshots.description: Vanilla patches are common in savannas, and the vanilla can be upright, sideways or hanging. Breaking vanilla without shears is a bad idea.
screenshots.title: Vanilla

screenshots.description: A picnic with some of the mod's food. Strawberries heal, chocolate makes you fast and then slow and vanilla stops you from receiving effects.
screenshots.title: Picnic

screenshots.description: Strawberry patches grow in the plains biome semi-commonly. They have some coarse dirt mixed in, which means some of the strawberries only get to their flowering stage.
screenshots.title: Strawberries

screenshots.description: Large groups of chimpanzees can occasionally be found near banana plants in jungles. They can often be seen grooming each other and shaking the bundles of banana plants for food. Being curious creatures, they love interacting with various items and blocks.
screenshots.title: Chimpanzees

screenshots.description: Chimpanzees will attack anything that attacks them. Additionally, shooting a bananarrow (crafted with an arrow and a banana) at any mob will provoke chimps to attack it.
screenshots.title: Strength in Numbers
